
[Annapolis, 24 Dec. 1783. Entry in SJL reads: J. Madison of the collegeto observe thermometer just before sunriseCrawfords theoryRittenhs orrery. Hopkinsons quilling. Not found, but see Madison to TJ, 22 Jan. 1784. Hopkinsons quilling: on 21 Nov. 1783 TJ attended a meeting of the American Philosophical Society at which Hopkinson presented a Plan and directions for improving the method of quilling an Harpsichord; a year later A paper containing further improvements in quilling a Harpsichord was presented by Mr. Hopkinson (minutes of the Am. Phil. Soc., 9 Dec. 1784, MS in PPAP; see Hopkinson to TJ, 25 May 1784).
